AMD spent its time at the Consumer Trade Association's CES tradeshow talking with the US Government about AI data center projects, talking with B2B partners about its server racks and solutions (like Helios), and ignoring the existence of its AMD Ryzen 9850X3D CPU that it literally just announced on its website. As tech executives scramble to keep the infinite money glitch flowing, we get to see a revolving door of AI companies selling the idea of servers to consumers.
